(10, 8, 8, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306027683, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Java programming guidelines', '<r><B><s>[b]</s>Indenting:<e>[/b]</e></B><br/>\n<br/>\nWe use the \"BSD KNF style\" for indenting. An example:<br/>\n\n<CODE><s>[code]</s>    \n                if ($foo == \'bar\') {\n                    something();\n                    elseif ($bar) {\n                        somethingElse();\n                    }\n                }\n<e>[/code]</e></CODE>\n\n<B><s>[b]</s>Dealing with warnings:<e>[/b]</e></B><br/>\n<br/>\nDo not write code that is riddled with warnings. Do not write code that suppresses warnings for no reason.<br/>\nExample of bad code:<br/>\n\n<CODE><s>[code]</s>    \n                    @SuppressWarnings(\"rawtypes\")\n                    List darkquest = new ArrayList();\n<e>[/code]</e></CODE>\n\nExample of good code:<br/>\n\n<CODE><s>[code]</s>        \n                    List&lt;String&gt; darkquest = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\n<e>[/code]</e></CODE>\n\n<br/>\n<B><s>[b]</s>Dealing with exceptions:<e>[/b]</e></B><br/>\n<br/>\nAll exceptions should be handled. This means do not surround your code with a try {} catch(Exception e) {} and hide exceptions. If your code throws errors, figure out why it does so. Do not catch the error and do nothing with it.<br/>\nUsing exceptions VS returning null<br/>\n<br/>\n    If you are always expecting to find a value then throw the exception if it is missing. The exception would mean that there was a problem.<br/>\n    If the value can be missing or present and both are valid for the application logic then return a null.<br/>\n<br/>\nThe benefits of using exceptions<br/>\n<br/>\nExceptions are more informative. If you throw new Exception(\'Argument 1 was null\'), the stack trace will include that as the reason. If you return a null, you will only get a NullPointerException<br/>\n<br/>\nException checking can be forced. This means if you write a function that may have an error in it, the person who uses your function will be forced by the compiler to handle the error. If you return a null, he might not handle it himself and the application will throw a NullPointerException / crash.<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<B><s>[b]</s>Documenting:<e>[/b]</e></B><br/>\n<br/>\nAt least all public methods must be documented with Javadoc. The more you document, the better.<br/>\n\n<CODE><s>[code]</s>                        \npackage org.darkquest.gs.model.snapshot;\n\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\n\n\n/**\n * Chat log class, stores chat string, time of message, message owner and set of players that saw the message\n * @author Pets\n *\n */\npublic class Chatlog extends Snapshot {\n\n    /**\n     * The messages that was sent\n     */\n    private String message;\n    /**\n     * Set of players that received the message;\n     */\n    private ArrayList recievers = new ArrayList();\n\n    /**\n     * Constructor\n     * @param sender player that sent the message\n     * @param chatstring the message that was sent\n     * @param recievers players that saw the message\n     *\n     */\n    public Chatlog(String sender, String chatstring, ArrayList recievers) {\n        super(sender);\n        this.message = chatstring;\n        this.recievers = recievers;\n    }\n    /**\n     * @return list of player names that saw the message\n     */\n    public ArrayList getRecievers() {\n        return recievers;\n    }\n    /**\n     * @return the message\n     */\n    public String getMessage() {\n        return message;\n    }\n}<e>[/code]</e></CODE></r>', '63d468fa8970b3d25bb4406ae6dd046e', 0, '', '2v6x524m', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(11, 9, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306027753, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Alternate exp formula for combat', '[quote=&quot;Latifundio&quot;:co5tec39]What this does:\n\nWith this low lvl mobs will give small exp and the higher lvl is a mob, the better exp it will give.\n\nThe problem with rscd current formula is that you get rewarded for fighting chickens and rats instead of being rewarded when you fight high lvl npc. Also is more fun training at the strongest enemy that oneself can handle.\n[code:co5tec39]public static int combatExperience(Mob mob) {\n    double exp = Math&#46;pow(mob&#46;getCombatLevel(), 2) * 1&#46;5D;\n    return (int) (mob instanceof Player ? (exp / 4D) &#58; exp);\n   }[/code:co5tec39]Note: This goes in Formulae.java and need to replace the old formula. Also exprate need to be set at 1 at Constants.java (and maybe Player.java) or it will give too much exp from lvl 100+ npcs.[/quote:co5tec39]', '0ab97c499da4012ca5e10ff57aa350d3', 0, 'gIA=', 'co5tec39', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(12, 10, 8, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306027965, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Animation ID Guide', '<r><QUOTE author=\"Latifundio\"><s>[quote=Latifundio]</s>I had lots of trouble finding how to change(or recolor) the sprites for armor and some NPC so i had to ID all the animation myself and comment some of them(for example ice warriors armor have their own animation even though it just look like mith)<br/>\n<br/>\nRemember this will just affect client side and you will find this extracting from Animations.rscd file<br/>\n<br/>\nNote that ice warriors get more bright armor and sword and giants now have chain mail and mace.<br/>\nand the ice queen now have white hair, rune b axe, rune shield and white cape <br/>\n\n<QUOTE author=\"MARWOLF\"><s>[QUOTE=MARWOLF]</s>Interesting. I\'ll have to look more into this. Whenever I tried I ended up with NPCs with huge heads.<e>[/quote]</e></QUOTE>\nYea, its very confusing since there are npc definitions both on database and client. For changing stats of the npc it needs to be done at the database but for the name, skin color, size and sprites, those are in the NPCs.rscd file.<br/>\n<br/>\nLets look at the messed up \"Chaos Druid Warrior\" ID 555<br/>\nLol this guy has 2 sprites for legs! (see blue from the pants?)<br/>\n\n<CODE><s>[code]</s>&lt;NPCDef&gt;\n    &lt;name&gt;Chaos Druid warrior&lt;/name&gt;\n    &lt;description&gt;A crazy evil druid&lt;/description&gt;\n    &lt;command&gt;&lt;/command&gt;\n    &lt;attack&gt;48&lt;/attack&gt;\n    &lt;strength&gt;42&lt;/strength&gt;\n    &lt;hits&gt;40&lt;/hits&gt;\n    &lt;defense&gt;48&lt;/defense&gt;\n    &lt;attackable&gt;true&lt;/attackable&gt;\n    &lt;aggressive&gt;true&lt;/aggressive&gt;\n    &lt;respawnTime&gt;30&lt;/respawnTime&gt;\n    &lt;sprites&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;6&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;2&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;122&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;84&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;42&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n    &lt;/sprites&gt;\n    &lt;hairColour&gt;1&lt;/hairColour&gt;\n    &lt;topColour&gt;65535&lt;/topColour&gt;\n    &lt;bottomColour&gt;255&lt;/bottomColour&gt;\n    &lt;skinColour&gt;15392466&lt;/skinColour&gt;\n    &lt;camera1&gt;145&lt;/camera1&gt;\n    &lt;camera2&gt;220&lt;/camera2&gt;<e>[/code]</e></CODE>3rd sprite is 2 (normal legs) bottom color is 255 (blue)<br/>\nbut in the 8th sprite is 42 (black platelegs) seems like someone forgot to -1 the 3rd sprite.<br/>\n122 is staff, and 84 is top wizardrobe red...<br/>\n<br/>\nLets fix this guy with a black chain and a black mace and red robe bottom<br/>\n\n<CODE><s>[code]</s>&lt;NPCDef&gt;\n    &lt;name&gt;Chaos Druid warrior&lt;/name&gt;\n    &lt;description&gt;A crazy evil druid&lt;/description&gt;\n    &lt;command&gt;&lt;/command&gt;\n    &lt;attack&gt;48&lt;/attack&gt;\n    &lt;strength&gt;42&lt;/strength&gt;\n    &lt;hits&gt;40&lt;/hits&gt;\n    &lt;defense&gt;48&lt;/defense&gt;\n    &lt;attackable&gt;true&lt;/attackable&gt;\n    &lt;aggressive&gt;true&lt;/aggressive&gt;\n    &lt;respawnTime&gt;30&lt;/respawnTime&gt;\n    &lt;sprites&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;6&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;2&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;121&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;26&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;90&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n    &lt;/sprites&gt;\n    &lt;hairColour&gt;1&lt;/hairColour&gt;\n    &lt;topColour&gt;15609904&lt;/topColour&gt;\n    &lt;bottomColour&gt;255&lt;/bottomColour&gt;\n    &lt;skinColour&gt;15392466&lt;/skinColour&gt;\n    &lt;camera1&gt;145&lt;/camera1&gt;\n    &lt;camera2&gt;220&lt;/camera2&gt;\n    &lt;walkModel&gt;6&lt;/walkModel&gt;\n    &lt;combatModel&gt;6&lt;/combatModel&gt;\n    &lt;combatSprite&gt;5&lt;/combatSprite&gt;<e>[/code]</e></CODE>121 is black mace, 26 black chain, 90 robes bottom and i also changed the top color for the shirt to red (should look more like a warrior now lol).<br/>\n<br/>\nFor bigger npc just increase camera1 and camera2 numbers.<e>[/quote]</e></QUOTE></r>', '4dc583199d66b4a917a62d1dd82bdc0b', 0, '', '3w02j0a8', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(19, 17, 11, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306028627, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', '(Wolf Kingdom) Death view', 'Going to remove the text overlay of &quot;you have died, oh deary me&quot; and instead put a timer so that the player will remain dead and laying there until the timer expires and then teleport them with health returned to respawn coordinates. This will let the player view what happens after they die as sometimes you want to see how things go down after you are killed during PK trips.\n\nThe timer will be a short term solution until a &quot;release&quot; button can be implemented similar to that in WoW.', 'bb37aa61342822f15b2886ee6264cf9e', 0, '', '2retefcu', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(22, 20, 8, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306029034, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', '2D Landscape Editor Guide', '<r>Common Tile Textures:<br/>\nIce: 0<br/>\nRegular Grass: 70<br/>\nBaby Grass: 23<br/>\nMedium Grass: 39<br/>\nDead Grass: 89<br/>\nDust: 111<br/>\nSand: 132<br/>\nDirt: 146<br/>\nMud: (128-158)<br/>\nPeat Moss: 168<br/>\nDead Ground: 183<br/>\nLava Stone: 206<br/>\n<br/>\nOverlays:<br/>\n0: Grass<br/>\n1: Road<br/>\n2: Water<br/>\n3: Wood floor<br/>\n4: Bridge<br/>\n5: Stone floor<br/>\n6: Bank floor<br/>\n8: Black hole<br/>\n9: Cliff<br/>\n11: Lava<br/>\n16: Black tile<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<B><s>[b]</s>2D Landscape Editor Guide:<e>[/b]</e></B><br/>\n<br/>\nGo to File &gt; Open<br/>\n<br/>\nSelect Landscape.rscd and click \"Open.\"<br/>\n<br/>\nThe landscape is built in sectors - squares that are glued together to form the entire landscape. The game loads the landscape in blocks to reduce lag. Choose a sector or click on a Preset town. You can even click \"Jump to coords\" to get to a specific spot you know in game.<br/>\n<br/>\nYou should see a map with colored dots. Those dots can be selected and info can be seen about them on the right side of the window. The XML files that store where and what these dots are - is not a live representation of what is in game. It is 95% accurate - I included the last known XML files before DarkQuest went fully database-driven and moved away from XML files with this Landscape editor build.<br/>\n<br/>\nWith a tile selected - tiles, that is what each square is called, click \"Advanced\" &gt; \"Toggle Tile Info\" - this will let you see additional information about that tile.<br/>\n<br/>\nElevation is a pain, this is a 2D editor and you cannot judge elevation unless you a.) test it out in a game client, or b.) very every tile on your sector is the right number for elevation.<br/>\n<br/>\nLuckily, for mass elevation/tile modification, a copy and paste function was built in. You can go to \"Edit\" &gt; \"Copy Tile\" and then find your new spot and do \"Edit\" &gt; \"Paste Tile.\"<br/>\n<br/>\nHow can you more quickly copy and paste tiles for large scale creation? First, click on the drop down menu on the right side of the Landscape editor and make sure it says \"None.\"<br/>\n<br/>\nNow find the tile you want to copy and click on it.<br/>\n<br/>\nGo back to the drop down menu on the right side of the Landscape editor and choose \"Configure your own.\"<br/>\n<br/>\nBelow, click on the button that reads \"Load data.\"<br/>\n<br/>\nThe sliders should now automatically match what the tile info displays. You can now click on other tiles and it will automatically use those settings from the \"copied\" tile. Be careful not to screw up tiles you already completed though and watch that elevation, its hard to judge.<br/>\n<br/>\nYou can stop it from automatically using tile data to make new tiles by selecting \"None\" from that drop down menu.<br/>\n<br/>\nSo how about moving to a sector adjacent to the one you are currently on. On the right hand side of the Landscape editor, click on the buttons labeled \"Up\", \"Down\", \"Left\", and \"Right.\" If you have not saved your sector and you click the directional buttons, it will ask you to save it first.<br/>\n<br/>\nRemember to save often! \"File\" &gt; \"Save Landscape.\"<br/>\n<br/>\nScrew it up? \"File\" &gt; \"Revert Landscape.\"<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\nSo now its time to test out your landscape. You need to copy this Landscape.rscd file into the client cache folder located in your \"Game/client/Cache\" folder. The game server uses the same Landscape.rscd file as the client does and you will need to copy it to \"Game/server/conf/server/data/\" (Make two identical copies, one named \"F2PLandscape.rscd\" and the other \"P2PLandscape.rscd\")</r>', '4cbaa27b1d3e77795848268a27ee9780', 0, '', '9ouow4e7', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(23, 21, 8, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306029099, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Game Commands', '<r>Updated 10/01/2018<br/>\n<br/>\n<I><s>[i]</s>Note: All commands trickle up to higher ranks<e>[/i]</e></I><br/>\n<br/>\n<B><s>[b]</s>Admin commands:<e>[/b]</e></B><br/>\n    item ID QUANTITY<br/>\n    bank<br/>\n    appearance<br/>\n    update SECONDS<br/>\n    shutdown<br/>\n    dropall<br/>\n    addbank<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<B><s>[b]</s>Developer/Mod commands:<e>[/b]</e></B><br/>\n    town NAME<br/>\n    mod<br/>\n    dev<br/>\n    mute<br/>\n    goto<br/>\n    summon<br/>\n    kick<br/>\n    ban<br/>\n    blink<br/>\n    teleport<br/>\n    invis<br/>\n    info<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<B><s>[b]</s>Regular user commands:<e>[/b]</e></B><br/>\n    help<br/>\n    commands<br/>\n    online<br/>\n    uniqueonline<br/>\n    onlinelist</r>', '7b69f96c434aa38d2f2d7137d72353d9', 0, '', 'q1v7ayfp', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(30, 29, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030449, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Dead trees', '[code:qmnzf5bt]import java&#46;util&#46;ArrayList;[/code:qmnzf5bt]\n\n[code:qmnzf5bt]case 88&#58; // Live trees\n                owner&#46;setBusy(true);\n                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;The tree seems to lash out at you!&quot;);\n                World&#46;getWorld()&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(owner) {\n                                public void action() {\n                                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;The tree seems to lash out at you!&quot;);\n                                int damage = owner&#46;getCurStat(3) / 5;    \n                                owner&#46;setLastDamage(damage);\n                                owner&#46;setCurStat(3, owner&#46;getCurStat(3) - damage);\n                                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendStat(3);\n                                ArrayList&lt;Player&gt; playersToInform = new ArrayList&lt;Player&gt;();\n                                playersToInform&#46;addAll(owner&#46;getViewArea()&#46;getPlayersInView());\n                                for (Player p &#58; playersToInform)\n                                        p&#46;informOfModifiedHits(owner);\n                                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You are badly scratched by the tree&quot;);  \n                                owner&#46;setBusy(false);\n                                                }\n                                });\n                                break;[/code:qmnzf5bt]', '3a1e0c3a1344ac9ab41f94d4dda96a85', 0, 'AIA=', 'qmnzf5bt', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(31, 30, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030512, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Sheep Ammy', '<!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QsJSexz5l34\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QsJSexz5l34</a><!-- m -->\n\nput this in your itemwieldabledef.xml\nthen equip item 1009\n\n[code:101kl0q9]\n\n        &lt;entry&gt;\n                &lt;int&gt;1009&lt;/int&gt;\n                &lt;ItemWieldableDef&gt;\n                        &lt;sprite&gt;130&lt;/sprite&gt;\n                        &lt;type&gt;1024&lt;/type&gt;\n                        &lt;wieldPos&gt;8&lt;/wieldPos&gt;\n                        &lt;armourPoints&gt;20&lt;/armourPoints&gt;\n                        &lt;weaponAimPoints&gt;0&lt;/weaponAimPoints&gt;\n                        &lt;weaponPowerPoints&gt;0&lt;/weaponPowerPoints&gt;\n                        &lt;magicPoints&gt;0&lt;/magicPoints&gt;\n                        &lt;prayerPoints&gt;0&lt;/prayerPoints&gt;\n                        &lt;rangePoints&gt;0&lt;/rangePoints&gt;\n                        &lt;requiredStats&gt;\n                        &lt;/requiredStats&gt;\n                        &lt;femaleOnly&gt;false&lt;/femaleOnly&gt;\n                &lt;/ItemWieldableDef&gt;\n        &lt;/entry&gt;\n[/code:101kl0q9]', '8cbde9891069c79fa895f6186d6c9740', 0, 'AIA=', '101kl0q9', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(32, 31, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030537, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Change client version in RSCA source', 'The fuckers hid it. The config class for CLIENT_VERSION= is fake.\n\nIt is hidden in the GameWindowMiddleMan class:\n\n[code:1l4q084v]    gameBoxPrint(&quot;Connection lost! Please wait&#46;&#46;&#46;&quot;,\n                        &quot;Attempting to re-establish&quot;);\n            else\n                loginScreenPrint(&quot;Please wait&#46;&#46;&#46;&quot;, &quot;Connecting to server&quot;);\n\n            streamClass = new StreamClass(makeSocket(Config&#46;SERVER_IP, Config&#46;SERVER_PORT), this);\n            streamClass&#46;maxPacketReadCount = maxPacketReadCount;\n            long l = DataOperations&#46;stringLength12ToLong(user);\n            streamClass&#46;createPacket(32);\n            streamClass&#46;addByte((int) (l &gt;&gt; 16 &amp; 31L));\n            // edit KO9\n            streamClass&#46;addString(&quot;ORG&#46;RSCANGEL&#46;CLIENT&#46;MUDCLIENT-W3B5&quot;);\n            // edit\n            streamClass&#46;finalisePacket();\n            long sessionID = streamClass&#46;read8ByteLong();\n            if (sessionID == 0L) {\n                loginScreenPrint(&quot;Login server offline&#46;&quot;,\n                        &quot;Please try again in a few mins&quot;);\n                return;\n            }\n            System&#46;out&#46;print(&quot;Session ID&#58; &quot; + sessionID);\n            int sessionRotationKeys&#91;&#93; = new int&#91;4&#93;;\n            sessionRotationKeys&#91;0&#93; = (int) (Math&#46;random() * 99999999D);\n            sessionRotationKeys&#91;1&#93; = (int) (Math&#46;random() * 99999999D);\n            sessionRotationKeys&#91;2&#93; = (int) (sessionID &gt;&gt; 32);\n            sessionRotationKeys&#91;3&#93; = (int) sessionID;\n            DataEncryption dataEncryption = new DataEncryption(new byte&#91;117&#93;);\n            if (reconnecting)\n                dataEncryption&#46;addByte(1);\n            else\n                dataEncryption&#46;addByte(0);\n            dataEncryption&#46;add4ByteInt(52);\n            dataEncryption&#46;add4ByteInt(sessionRotationKeys&#91;0&#93;);\n            dataEncryption&#46;add4ByteInt(sessionRotationKeys&#91;1&#93;);\n            dataEncryption&#46;add4ByteInt(sessionRotationKeys&#91;2&#93;);\n            dataEncryption&#46;add4ByteInt(sessionRotationKeys&#91;3&#93;);\n            dataEncryption&#46;addString(user);\n            dataEncryption&#46;addString(pass);[/code:1l4q084v]See that?\n[code:1l4q084v]            dataEncryption&#46;add4ByteInt(52);[/code:1l4q084v]Change the 52 to whatever version your server is and it will work.', 'e1d074bfe0c26b1fdab228355bbf5726', 0, 'AIA=', '1l4q084v', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(33, 32, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030559, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Removing empty vials', 'This will basically remove empty vials out of your inventory once you have finished all doses of the potion. In your InvActionHandler class, find:\n\n[code:26q84e8q]\n                owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;remove(item);\n                owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;add(new InvItem(newItem));\n                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendInventory();\n                owner&#46;setBusy(false);\n[/code:26q84e8q]Now the part you want to look at is the \'newItem\'. As this is the int used to identify the new item to be added, above that line, you want to add a check to see if the newItem being added is the empty vial.\n\n[code:26q84e8q]\n                if(newItem == 465) { // Empty vial ID\n                    owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;remove(newItem); // Remove the newItem\n                    owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendInventory(); // Send the inventory\n                    owner&#46;setBusy(false); // Make sure you set the player\'s busy status\n                } else {\n                    owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;remove(item);\n                    owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;add(new InvItem(newItem));\n                    owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendInventory();\n                    owner&#46;setBusy(false);\n                }\n            }\n[/code:26q84e8q]', '2ab739f204b3ec4d7601f5e3d3bc74a3', 0, 'AIA=', '26q84e8q', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(34, 33, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030582, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Charged dragonstone ammy', 'Here is pretty much a replica of the real RSC Dragonstone Amulet. This has been wrote for my new source that is currently in development.\n\n[code:2u79mk6j]\n                        case 597&#58; // Charged Dragonstone Amulet\n                            player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You rub the amulet&quot;);\n                            world&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(player) {\n                                public void action() {\n                                    player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;Where would you like to teleport to?&quot;);\n                                    world&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new MiniEvent(player) {\n                                        public void action() {\n                                            String&#91;&#93; teleportLocations = new String&#91;&#93; { &quot;Edgeville&quot;, &quot;Karamja&quot;, &quot;Draynor village&quot;, &quot;Al Kharid&quot;, &quot;Nowhere&quot; };\n                                            owner&#46;setMenuHandler(new MenuHandler(teleportLocations) {\n                                                public void handleReply(final int option, final String reply) {\n                                                    /**\n                                                     * Check to see if the player is already\n                                                     * busy or the item has a null value\n                                                     */\n                                                    if((owner&#46;isBusy()) || (owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;get(item) == null)) {\n                                                        return;\n                                                    }\n                                                    /**\n                                                     * Check the player\'s location to make sure\n                                                     * they aren\'t in the modroom or wilderness\n                                                     */\n                                                    if((owner&#46;getLocation()&#46;wildernessLevel() &gt;= 30) || (owner&#46;getLocation()&#46;inModRoom())) {\n                                                        owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;A magical force stops you from teleporting&#46;&quot;);\n                                                        return;\n                                                    }\n                                                    owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendSound(&quot;spellok&quot;);\n                                                    switch(option) {\n                                                        case 0&#58; // Edgeville\n                                                            owner&#46;teleport(226, 447, true);\n                                                            break;\n                                                        case 1&#58; // Karamja\n                                                            owner&#46;teleport(360, 696, true);\n                                                            break;\n                                                        case 2&#58; // Draynor Village\n                                                            owner&#46;teleport(214, 632, true);\n                                                            break;\n                                                        case 3&#58; // Al Kharid\n                                                            owner&#46;teleport(72, 696, true);\n                                                            break;\n                                                        case 4&#58; // Nowhere\n                                                            break;\n                                                        default&#58;\n                                                            return;\n                                                        }\n                                                        if((DataConversions&#46;random(0, 5) == 1) &amp;&amp; (owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;remove(item) &gt; -1)) {\n                                                            owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;add(new InvItem(DRAGONSTONE_AMULET, 1));\n                                                            owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendInventory();\n                                                        }\n                                                    }\n                                                });\n                                                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMenu(teleportLocations);\n                                            }\n                                        });\n                                    }\n                                });\n                                break;\n[/code:2u79mk6j]', '636529b04798e53a71f86c1a5dc3ef2f', 0, 'AIA=', '2u79mk6j', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(35, 34, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030645, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Cooking', '<!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=339.0\">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=339.0</a><!-- m -->\n\n<!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=338.0\">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=338.0</a><!-- m -->\n\n<!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=336.0\">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=336.0</a><!-- m -->\n\n<!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=337.0\">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=337.0</a><!-- m -->\n\n<!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=335.0\">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=335.0</a><!-- m -->\n\n<!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=332.0\">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=332.0</a><!-- m -->', 'acdcb0f79d22b0077d3ac27025ad518c', 0, '', '2660r4wh', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(36, 35, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030713, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Zombie world event', '<!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.moparscape.org/smf/index.php/topic,449905.0.html\">http://www.moparscape.org/smf/index.php ... 905.0.html</a><!-- m -->', 'a5048c52bac9101c25a8b5cef8eebb10', 0, '', '45rpfg3w', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(37, 36, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030772, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Marble minigame', 'Posted by Yong Min.\n\nSticking with the minigame theme, here is my take on the thieving minigame for marbles. If you want to change the required thieving level and the ID of your marble item, you can do that in the Marbles class.\n\n[code:2tboitxn]\n   public static int REQUIRED_LEVEL = 85;\n   public static int THIEVING_ID = 17; // DO NOT CHANGE\n   public static int MARBLE_ID = 1330;[/code:2tboitxn]^Do NOT change the THIEVING_ID.\n\nIn your \'minigames\' folder, add the Marbles class:\n\n[code:2tboitxn]\npackage org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;minigames;\n\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;entityhandling&#46;EntityHandler;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;util&#46;DataConversions;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;event&#46;ShortEvent;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;model&#46;InvItem;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;model&#46;Player;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;model&#46;World;\n\nimport java&#46;util&#46;List;\n\npublic class Marbles {\n   /**\n    * Thieving Minigame\n    * @author Yong Min\n    */\n   public static final World world = World&#46;getWorld();\n  \n   public static int REQUIRED_LEVEL = 85;\n   public static int THIEVING_ID = 17; // DO NOT CHANGE\n   public static int MARBLE_ID = 1330;\n  \n   public static void handleMarbleChest(final Player player) {\n      player&#46;setBusy(true);\n      world&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(player) {\n         public void action() {\n            if(player&#46;getInventory()&#46;countId(MARBLE_ID) &gt; 4) {\n               player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You open the chest&#46;&#46;&#46;&quot;);\n               player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You steal some marbles&#46;&quot;);\n               player&#46;getInventory()&#46;remove(MARBLE_ID, 5);\n               List&lt;InvItem&gt; loot = getMarbleChestLoot();\n               for(InvItem i &#58; loot) {\n                  if((i&#46;getAmount() &gt; 1) &amp;&amp; (!i&#46;getDef()&#46;isStackable())) {\n                     for(int x = 0; x &lt; i&#46;getAmount(); x++) {\n                        player&#46;getInventory()&#46;add(new InvItem(i&#46;getID(), 1));\n                     }\n                  } else {\n                     player&#46;getInventory()&#46;add(i);\n                  }\n               }\n               player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendInventory();\n            } else {\n               player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You don\'t have enough marbles!&quot;);\n            }\n            player&#46;setBusy(false);\n         }\n      });\n   }\n        \n   public static void checkThievingLevel(Player player) {\n      if(player&#46;getMaxStat(THIEVING_ID) &lt; REQUIRED_LEVEL) {\n         player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You need a thieving level of &quot; + REQUIRED_LEVEL + &quot; to thieve this chest!&quot;);\n      } else {\n         handleMarbleChest(player);\n      }\n      return;\n   }\n  \n   public static List&lt;InvItem&gt; getMarbleChestLoot() {\n      List&lt;InvItem&gt;&#91;&#93; possibleLoots = (List&lt;InvItem&gt;&#91;&#93;)EntityHandler&#46;getMarbleChestLoot();\n      return possibleLoots&#91;DataConversions&#46;random(0, possibleLoots&#46;length - 1)&#93;;\n   }\n}[/code:2tboitxn]Now in your ObjectAction class, find:\n\n[code:2tboitxn]\ncase 142&#58; // Black Knight Big Door[/code:2tboitxn]Above that, add:\n\n[code:2tboitxn]\n                  case 1189&#58; // Marble Chest\n                     Marbles&#46;checkThievingLevel(owner);\n                     break;[/code:2tboitxn]^Make sure you change the \'1189\' to whatever your chest ID is!\n\nNow in your EntityHandler class, find:\n\n[code:2tboitxn]\nprivate static List&#91;&#93; keyChestLoots;[/code:2tboitxn]Under that, add:\n\n[code:2tboitxn]\nprivate static List&#91;&#93; marbleChestLoots;[/code:2tboitxn]Now find:\n\n[code:2tboitxn]\n   public static List&#91;&#93; getKeyChestLoots() {\n      return keyChestLoots&#46;clone();\n   }[/code:2tboitxn]Under that, add:\n\n[code:2tboitxn]\n   public static List&#91;&#93; getMarbleChestLoot() {\n      return marbleChestLoots&#46;clone();\n   }[/code:2tboitxn]Now find:\n\n[code:2tboitxn]\nkeyChestLoots = (List&#91;&#93;)PersistenceManager&#46;load(&quot;defs/extras/KeyChestLoot&#46;xml&#46;gz&quot;);[/code:2tboitxn]Under that, add:\n\n[code:2tboitxn]\nmarbleChestLoots = (List&#91;&#93;)PersistenceManager&#46;load(&quot;defs/extras/MarbleChestLoot&#46;xml&#46;gz&quot;);[/code:2tboitxn]Now in your conf/defs/extras folder (server side), add the following file: <!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://uppit.com/8ux79hanwdti/MarbleChestLoot.xml.gz\">http://uppit.com/8ux79hanwdti/MarbleChestLoot.xml.gz</a><!-- m -->\n\nNote: You will need to change the ID of your marble within that file too. You can add any loot entry as you please.\n\nHere is the marble XML entry:\n\n[code:2tboitxn]\n  &lt;ItemDef&gt;\n    &lt;name&gt;Marble&lt;/name&gt;\n    &lt;description&gt;I wonder what this is used for&#46;&#46;&lt;/description&gt;\n    &lt;command&gt;&lt;/command&gt;\n    &lt;sprite&gt;102&lt;/sprite&gt;\n    &lt;basePrice&gt;4&lt;/basePrice&gt;\n    &lt;stackable&gt;true&lt;/stackable&gt;\n    &lt;wieldable&gt;false&lt;/wieldable&gt;\n    &lt;pictureMask&gt;10072780&lt;/pictureMask&gt;\n  &lt;/ItemDef&gt;[/code:2tboitxn]And here is the XML entry for the Marble Chest:\n\n[code:2tboitxn]\n  &lt;GameObjectDef&gt;\n    &lt;name&gt;Marble Chest&lt;/name&gt;\n    &lt;description&gt;Costs 5 marbles to open&lt;/description&gt;\n    &lt;command1&gt;Open&lt;/command1&gt;\n    &lt;command2&gt;Examine&lt;/command2&gt;\n    &lt;type&gt;1&lt;/type&gt;\n    &lt;width&gt;1&lt;/width&gt;\n    &lt;height&gt;1&lt;/height&gt;\n    &lt;groundItemVar&gt;0&lt;/groundItemVar&gt;\n    &lt;objectModel&gt;ChestClosed&lt;/objectModel&gt;\n  &lt;/GameObjectDef&gt;[/code:2tboitxn]', '5c3f1ab4920ca1832ec93f7a34ea641d', 0, 'AIA=', '2tboitxn', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(38, 37, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030837, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Bot protection', 'In your SessionRequest class, find:\n\n[code:oiiep6gl]\nplayer&#46;setClassName(p&#46;readString()&#46;trim());[/code:oiiep6gl]Under that, add:\n\n[code:oiiep6gl]\n      if(!player&#46;getClassName()&#46;equals(&quot;&amp;%&#46;&#46;&#46;&quot;)) {\n         System&#46;out&#46;println(player&#46;getUsername() + &quot; didn\'t equal the class name code!&quot;);\n         return;\n      }[/code:oiiep6gl]Now open your GameWindowMiddleMan class (client side), and find:\n\n[code:oiiep6gl]streamClass&#46;addString(this&#46;getClass()&#46;getName()&#46;toUpperCase());[/code:oiiep6gl]Replace that with:\n\n[code:oiiep6gl]streamClass&#46;addString(&quot;&amp;%&#46;&#46;&#46;&quot;);[/code:oiiep6gl]', '1c4799cef97ac70b856e585332239945', 0, 'AIA=', 'oiiep6gl', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(39, 38, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030910, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Kill stealing prevention', '<!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=302.0\">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=302.0</a><!-- m -->', '3e297c1a56339f831938b881356c2a18', 0, '', '1dluirm9', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(40, 39, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030933, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Darkquest plugin system', 'Some of you might have heard that I\'m restarting DarkQuest with RSCAs source, and that\'s true. I could use some help though, with plugin developers. There were some requests for a RuneCrafting skill on darkquest forums, and since the plugin system is as far as it is, perhaps you could write the skill?\n\n[code:ew2k635r]package org&#46;darkquest&#46;gs&#46;plugins&#46;plugs&#46;skills;\n\nimport java&#46;util&#46;Arrays;\n\nimport org&#46;darkquest&#46;gs&#46;model&#46;GameObject;\nimport org&#46;darkquest&#46;gs&#46;model&#46;InvItem;\nimport org&#46;darkquest&#46;gs&#46;model&#46;Player;\nimport org&#46;darkquest&#46;gs&#46;plugins&#46;listeners&#46;ItemOnObjectListener;\nimport org&#46;darkquest&#46;gs&#46;plugins&#46;listeners&#46;ObjectListener;\n\n/**\n * Handles RuneCrafting\n * @author You?\n *\n */\npublic class RuneCrafting implements ObjectListener, ItemOnObjectListener {\n    \n    static int&#91;&#93; objectIDs;\n    static int&#91;&#93; itemIDs;\n    static {\n        objectIDs = new int&#91;&#93;{};\n        itemIDs = new int&#91;&#93;{};\n        Arrays&#46;sort(objectIDs);\n        Arrays&#46;sort(itemIDs);\n    }\n    /**\n     * Determines if the object is associated\n     *\n     * ObjectAction&#58; this is basically called when someone clicks on an object (to determine if its associated)\n     * If true, onObjectAction is called\n     */\n    @Override\n    public boolean isObjectAssosiated(int objID, String command) {\n        /**\n         * Searches through the objectIDs, if found then\n         */\n        if(Arrays&#46;binarySearch(objectIDs, objID) &gt;= 0) {\n            return true;\n        }\n        /**\n         * This is just an example, basically this will force the onObjectAction method to be called if the command equals craft\n         */\n        if(command&#46;equalsIgnoreCase(&quot;craft&quot;)) {\n            return true;\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n    /**\n     * This should handle all the objectaction and return true if handled\n     */\n    @Override\n    public boolean onObjectAction(GameObject obj, String command, Player player) {\n        // TODO Auto-generated method stub\n        return false;\n    }\n\n\n    /**\n     * Determines if the invitem used on object is associated\n     *\n     * InvUseOnObject&#58; this is basically called when someone uses an invitem on an object (to determine if its associated)\n     * If true, onItemOnObjectAction is called\n     */\n    @Override\n    public boolean isItemOnObjectAssociated(int objID, int itemID) {\n        if(Arrays&#46;binarySearch(objectIDs, objID) &gt;= 0) {\n            return true;\n        }\n        if(Arrays&#46;binarySearch(itemIDs, itemID) &gt;= 0) {\n            return true;\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n    /**\n     * This should handle all the InvUseOnObject action and return true if handled\n     */\n    @Override\n    public boolean onItemOnObjectAction(GameObject obj, InvItem item, Player player) {\n        // TODO Auto-generated method stub\n        return false;\n    }\n}[/code:ew2k635r]A small tutorial:\n\nIf you want something to happen when someone clicks on a lever (ids: 122 and 123) then all you do is :\nReplace:\n\n[code:ew2k635r]objectIDs = new int&#91;&#93;{};[/code:ew2k635r]with\n\n[code:ew2k635r]objectIDs = new int&#91;&#93;{ 122, 123 };[/code:ew2k635r]And replace:\n[code:ew2k635r]\n@Override\n    public boolean onObjectAction(GameObject obj, String command, Player player) {\n        // TODO Auto-generated method stub\n        return false;\n    }[/code:ew2k635r]With:\n[code:ew2k635r]\n@Override\n    public boolean onObjectAction(GameObject obj, String command, Player player) {\n        System&#46;out&#46;println(&quot;Clicked lever!&quot;);\n        return true;\n    }[/code:ew2k635r]', 'dd41e75f30f4b093dc01dcaa9740ab89', 0, 'AIA=', 'ew2k635r', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(41, 40, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030960, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Scammer for Towelon quest', '[code:2amjnz9e]NpcTalk(&quot;Greetings Kind Sir!&quot;);\nWait(500);\nPlayerTalk(&quot;Yes?&quot;);\nWait(500);\nNpcTalk(&quot;You seem like someone who knows value!&quot;);\nWait(500);\nPlayerTalk(&quot;Huh?&quot;);\nWait(500);\nSendMessage(&quot;You realize this man must be a scammer&quot;);\nWait(500);\nNpcTalk(&quot;What would you say if I offered you&quot;);\nNpcTalk(&quot;the deal of a life time?&quot;);\nWait(1000);\nPlayerTalk(&quot;I would have to think about that&quot;);\nWait(500);\nNpcTalk(&quot;What if I said this deal would vanish tomorrow?&quot;);\nWait(500);\nPlayerTalk(&quot;Then I would demand you reach your point!&quot;);\nWait(500);\nNpcTalk(&quot;Yes yes&#46;&#46; see I have come across a purple cloth&quot;);\nNpcTalk(&quot;One which is fit for royalty, no other like it exists in all the land&quot;);\nWait(1000);\nPlayerTalk(&quot;That sounds interesting&#46; May I see it?&quot;);\nWait(500);\nNpcTalk(&quot;No, a dragon guards this&#46; I can tell you the location of this dragon!&quot;);\nWait(1000);\nPlayerTalk(&quot;For a hefty price, right?&quot;);\nWait(500);\nNpcTalk(&quot;Oh no, just a mere fee, nothing more&quot;);\nWait(500);\nPlayerTalk(&quot;How much do you ask?&quot;);\nNpcTalk(&quot;Oh but a small sum of only 50,000 gold coins!&quot;);[/code:2amjnz9e]', '0a0850151de9d7f81b9968b028da71e8', 0, 'AIA=', '2amjnz9e', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(42, 41, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306031014, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'RSCE cook handler', '[code:uhqjq03v]package server&#46;npchandler;\n\nimport server&#46;DelayedEventHandler;\nimport server&#46;Server;\nimport server&#46;event&#46;ShortEvent;\nimport server&#46;model&#46;ChatMessage;\nimport server&#46;model&#46;Inventory;\nimport server&#46;model&#46;MenuHandler;\nimport server&#46;model&#46;Npc;\nimport server&#46;model&#46;Player;\nimport server&#46;model&#46;World;\nimport server&#46;packetbuilder&#46;client&#46;MiscPacketBuilder;\n\npublic class Cook implements NpcHandler {\n   private static byte QUEST_ID = 0;\n   private static int EGG_ID = 19;\n   private static int MILK_ID = 22;\n   private static int FLOUR_ID = 136;\n  \n   public void handleNpc(Npc npc, Player player) throws Exception {\n      player&#46;setBusy(true);\n      switch(player&#46;getQuestCompletionStage(QUEST_ID)) {\n         case 0&#58;\n            player&#46;informOfNpcMessage(new ChatMessage(npc, &quot;Do you have my ingredients?&quot;, player));\n            Server&#46;requestWorldAccess()&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(player, npc) {\n               public void action() {\n                  owner&#46;setBusy(false);\n                  String&#91;&#93; options = { &quot;Yes, here they are&#46;&quot;, &quot;No, not yet&#46;&quot; };\n                  owner&#46;setMenuHandler(new MenuHandler(options) {\n                     public void handleReply(int option, String reply) {\n                        if(owner&#46;isBusy()) {\n                           return;\n                        }\n                        owner&#46;informOfChatMessage(new ChatMessage(owner, reply, npc));\n                        owner&#46;setBusy(true);\n                        Server&#46;requestWorldAccess()&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(owner, option) {\n                           public void action() {\n                              switch(option) {\n                                 case 0&#58;\n                                    Server&#46;requestWorldAccess()&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(owner) {\n                                       public void action() {\n                                          if((owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;countId(EGG_ID) &lt; 1) || (owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;countId(FLOUR_ID) &lt; 1) || (owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;countId(MILK_ID) &lt; 1)) {\n                                             owner&#46;informOfNpcMessage(new ChatMessage(npc, &quot;You don\'t have all of the ingredients, return when you do&#46;&quot;, owner));\n                                          } else {\n                                             owner&#46;informOfNpcMessage(new ChatMessage(npc, &quot;Thanks, &quot; + owner&#46;getUsername() + &quot; you\'re a real friend&#46;&quot;, owner));\n                                             owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;remove(EGG_ID, 1);\n                                             owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;remove(FLOUR_ID, 1);\n                                             owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;remove(MILK_ID, 1);\n                                             owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendInventory();\n                                             owner&#46;incQuestCompletionStage(QUEST_ID);\n                                             completeQuest(owner);\n                                          }\n                                       }\n                                    });\n                                 case 1&#58;\n                                    Server&#46;requestWorldAccess()&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(owner) {\n                                       public void action() {\n                                          owner&#46;informOfNpcMessage(new ChatMessage(owner, options&#91;1&#93;, npc));\n                                       }\n                                    });\n                                 }\n                                 owner&#46;setBusy(false);\n                                 npc&#46;unblock();\n                              }\n                           });\n                        }\n                     });\n                     owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMenu(options);\n                  }\n               });\n               break;\n            case 1\n               player&#46;informOfNpcMessage(new ChatMessage(npc, &quot;Thanks for getting me out of that pickle, &quot; + player&#46;getUsername() + &quot;&#46;&quot;, player));\n               break;\n            default&#58;\n               player&#46;informOfNpcMessage(new ChatMessage(npc, &quot;Help me make my cake?&quot;, player));\n               Server&#46;requestWorldAccess()&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(player, npc) {\n                  public void action() {\n                     owner&#46;setBusy(false);\n                     String&#91;&#93; options = { &quot;Yes, I will help you&#46;&quot;, &quot;Sorry, but I do not have the time&#46;&quot; };\n                     owner&#46;setMenuHandler(new MenuHandler(options) {\n                        public void handleReply(int option, String reply) {\n                           if(owner&#46;isBusy()) {\n                              return;\n                           }\n                           owner&#46;informOfChatMessage(new ChatMessage(owner, reply, npc));\n                           owner&#46;setBusy(true);\n                           Server&#46;requestWorldAccess()&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(owner, option) {\n                              public void action() {\n                                 switch(option) {\n                                    case 0&#58;\n                                       Server&#46;requestWorldAccess()&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(owner) {\n                                          public void action() {\n                                             owner&#46;informOfNpcMessage(new ChatMessage(owner, options&#91;0&#93;, npc));\n                                             owner&#46;addQuest(QUEST_ID);\n                                             owner&#46;informOfNpcMessage(new ChatMessage(npc, &quot;Thanks! I\'ll need an egg, a bucket of milk, and a pot of flour&#46;&quot;, owner));\n                                          }\n                                       });\n                                    case 1&#58;\n                                       Server&#46;requestWorldAccess()&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(owner) {\n                                          public void action() {\n                                             owner&#46;informOfNpcMessage(new ChatMessage(owner, options&#91;1&#93;, npc));\n                                          }\n                                       });\n                                    }\n                                    owner&#46;setBusy(false);\n                                    npc&#46;unblock();\n                                 }\n                              });\n                           }\n                        });\n                        owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMenu(options);\n                     }\n                  });\n               }\n               player&#46;setBusy(false);\n            }\n            \n            public void completeQuest(Player player) {\n               player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;@gre@You have completed The Cook\'s Assistant!&quot;);\n            }\n         }\n[/code:uhqjq03v]', '0da5fd504644906992ceeee287f35a41', 0, 'AIA=', 'uhqjq03v', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0);
