(170, 150, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318297822, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'on-demand client MP3 player', '<r>I was messing around with the RSCA source (because I was bored), and noticed they had a Mp3 class in the client, so I decided to make use of it.<br/>\n<br/>\nWhat I did was make it so that you issue a command, and it makes the client play a Mp3.  If they don\'t have it, it downloads it into the cache folder, and will load each time the client starts.<br/>\n<br/>\nServer side:<br/>\n<br/>\nIn MiscPacketBuilder class add:\n<CODE><s>[code]</s><i>\n</i>        public void sendMP3(String soundName) {\n                RSCPacketBuilder s = new RSCPacketBuilder();\n                s.setID(22);\n                s.addBytes(soundName.getBytes());\n                packets.add(s.toPacket());\n        }<e>[/code]</e></CODE>\n\nIn the CommandHandler class add:\n<CODE><s>[code]</s><i>\n</i>        if(cmd.equals(\"sound\")) {\n                StringBuilder command = new StringBuilder();\n                for(String s : args)\n                        command.append(s);\n                for (Player p : world.getPlayers())\n                        p.getActionSender().sendMP3(new String(command));\n                return;\n        }<e>[/code]</e></CODE>\n\nIn the client:<br/>\n<br/>\nIn the mudclient class, look for:\n<CODE><s>[code]</s><i>\n</i>if (command == 22) {<e>[/code]</e></CODE>\n\nInside that statement, make it look like this:\n<CODE><s>[code]</s><i>\n</i>                                String s = new String(data, 1, length - 1);\n                                Mp3 t;\n                                String name = s.substring(s.lastIndexOf(\'/\') + 1);\n                                if (MP3Sounds.containsKey(name)) {\n                                        t = new Mp3(MP3Sounds.get(name).getPath());\n                                } else {\n                                        File f = downloadFile(s, \".\" + File.separator + \"rsca\" + File.separator + name);\n                                        MP3Sounds.put(name, f);\n                                        t = new Mp3(f.getPath());\n                                }\n                                t.play();\n                                return;<e>[/code]</e></CODE>\n\nAdd this method into the mudclient class:\n<CODE><s>[code]</s><i>\n</i>        private File downloadFile(String src, String dest) {\n                BufferedInputStream in;\n                try {\n                        in = new BufferedInputStream(new URL(src).openStream());\n                        File file = new File(dest);\n                        if (!file.exists())\n                                file.createNewFile();\n                        FileOutputStream fos = new FileOutputStream(dest);\n                        BufferedOutputStream bout = new BufferedOutputStream(fos, 1024);\n                        byte data[] = new byte[1024];\n                        while (in.read(data, 0, 1024) &gt;= 0) {\n                                bout.write(data);\n                        }\n                        bout.close();\n                        in.close();\n                } catch (MalformedURLException e) {\n                        e.printStackTrace();\n                } catch (IOException e) {\n                        e.printStackTrace();\n                }\n                return new File(dest);\n        }<e>[/code]</e></CODE>\n\nRename the ctfsounds hashmap to, \"MP3Sounds\".<br/>\n<br/>\nMake the loadSounds method in the mudclient class look like this:\n<CODE><s>[code]</s><i>\n</i>        private final void loadSounds() {\n                try {\n                        drawDownloadProgress(\"Unpacking Sound effects\", 90, false);\n                        sounds = load(\"sounds1.mem\");\n                        audioReader = new AudioReader();\n                        File dir = new File(\".\" + File.separator + \"rsca\");\n                        String[] chldrn = dir.list();\n\n                        FilenameFilter filter = new FilenameFilter() {\n                                public boolean accept(File dir, String name) {\n                                        return name.endsWith(\".mp3\");\n                                }\n                        };\n                        \n                        chldrn = dir.list(filter);\n                        for (final String s : chldrn) {\n                                new Thread(new Runnable() {\n                                        public void run() {\n                                                MP3Sounds.put(s, mudclient.loadCachedFile(s));\n                                        }\n                                }).start();\n                        }\n                        return;\n                } catch (Throwable throwable) {\n                        System.out.println(\"Unable to init sounds:\" + throwable);\n                }\n        }<e>[/code]</e></CODE>\n\nAlso, make sure you don\'t forget to import the correct packages.<br/>\n<br/>\nAn example usage would be ::sound <URL url=\"http://google.com/rickroll.mp3\">http://google.com/rickroll.mp3</URL><br/>\n<br/>\nAdditional benefits of this:<br/>\nYou can drop mp3s into the cache directory, and the client will load them.<br/>\nYou can play mp3s with a simple command.<br/>\nYou now have the ability to easily implement  other things that require downloading files from a url.</r>', '571c4b4e77fa2ab3f94beb398bb5b48b', 0, 'AIA=', '2e501nmt', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0);
